# aarch64 Initrd Installer Helpers

## Arch Linux `aarch64`

```bash
sudo ./generate_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer
./publish_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer
sudo ./test_archlinux_aarch64_initrd_installer
```

The test wrapper creates a disposable copy of the built image, replaces the boot kernel and initramfs with the generated installer artifacts while preserving the target boot file names, optionally wipes everything except `/boot`, and then runs the normal `../test_archlinux_aarch64_image` QEMU flow.

Set `WIPE_ROOT=0` if you want to keep the original root filesystem for a lighter test.

See [../../README](../../README) for the final image build/test/publish commands, and [../../common/initrd_installer/README](../../common/initrd_installer/README) for the shared initrd installer notes.
